          "alt": null,
          "title": "IMG_2831"
        }}></img></a></p>
    <p>{`A little bit further down the river we crossed Pont Neuf to the island that Paris was founded on in, something like, 52 B.C. We were then suppose to see Sainte Chappelle and their amazing stain glass windows, but some man was only letting people in with tickets, and wouldn’t provide information where you could buy them saying it was too late. (it was 35 minutes before they closed). So that was a tad disappointing, but we quickly forgot about that when we walked over to Notre Dame de Paris where again we were able to marvel in architectural beauty, and then enter the cathedral (where they were about to conduct an actual mass). This turned out to be great timing, as we got to see the cathedral in action with live singers, priest, incense burning, etc. They also weren’t too shabby on the stain glass windows.`}<span style="text-align: center;">{` `}</span></p>
